description.p:
A second group of interesting compounds consists of those compounds of formula (I) wherein one or more of the following restrictions apply:


a) L2 is a direct bond or a bivalent radical selected from —C1-6alkanediyl- or —C(O)—C1-6alkanediyl-;

b) Z is hydrogen or a radical selected from (a-1), (a-4) or (a-5).
